%>

<h1>Using OBS download pages</h1>

<p>Welcome to the OBS download page. This page offers a simple way to show your users the latest
  builds of your packages and appliances by either embedding its output as an iframe in your project homepage,
  or by creating a download page for you.</p>

<h3>Creating a download page for a package</h3>

<p>Just create a link to </p>
<pre>https://software.opensuse.org/download/package?project=<b>&lt;projectname&gt;</b>&amp;package=<b>&lt;packagename&gt;</b></pre>
<p>for example: <%= link_to "/download/package?project=openSUSE:Tools&amp;package=osc", :controller => :download, :action => :package, :project => "openSUSE:Tools", :package => "osc" %>
</p>

<p>To embed this page as an iframe in the download section of your project homepage, you can use this code: </p>

<pre>
&lt;iframe src="https://software.opensuse.org/download/package.iframe?project=<b>&lt;projectname&gt;</b>&amp;package=<b>&lt;packagename&gt;</b>"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
</pre>

<p>Which will result in an output like this: </p>

<iframe src="<%= url_for :controller => :download, :action => :package, :project => "openSUSE:Tools", :package => "osc", :format => "iframe" %>" width="100%" height="700px" frameBorder="0" ></iframe>

<h3>Creating a download page for a pattern</h3>

<p>Linking to a pattern is similar to the way described above for a package, just change the url to use <i>pattern</i>:</p>

<pre>https://software.opensuse.org/download/pattern?project=<b>&lt;projectname&gt;</b>&amp;pattern=<b>&lt;patternname&gt;</b></pre>

<h3>Creating a download page for an appliance</h3>

<p>If your OBS project is building appliances, you can also link to those with: </p>

<pre>https://software.opensuse.org/download/appliance?project=<b>&lt;projectname&gt;</b></pre>

<p>To embed an iframe showing the appliances of your project, use this code: </p>

<pre>
&lt;iframe src="https://software.opensuse.org/download/appliance.iframe?project=<b>&lt;projectname&gt;</b>"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
</pre>

<p>Which will result in an output like this: </p>

<iframe src="<%= url_for :controller => :download, :action => :appliance, :project => "OBS:Server:2.8", :format => "iframe" %>" width="100%" height="700px" frameBorder="0"></iframe>

<h2>Advanced options</h2>

<p><b>JSON output:</b> You can also request the data in json format by using .json as output format, for example:
  <%= link_to "/download/package.json?project=openSUSE:Tools&package=obs-server", :controller => :download, :action => :package, :format => :json, :project => "openSUSE:Tools", :package => "obs-server" %>.
</p>

  <p>
  <b>Theming: </b>
  To customize the theming of the download page, you have multiple options to change the colors.
  Use the parameters <b>bcolor</b>, <b>fcolor</b>, <b>hcolor</b> and <b>acolor</b> to set the different colors. <br/>
  Example:
    <%= link_to "/download/appliance.iframe?project=openSUSE:Tools&fcolor=607890&hcolor=607890&acolor=607890&bcolor=123", :controller => :download, :action => :appliance, :format => :iframe, :project => "openSUSE:Tools", :fcolor => "607890", :hcolor => "607890", :acolor => "607890", :bcolor => "123" %>
  </p>
  <iframe src="<%= url_for :controller => :download, :action => :package, :fcolor => "ffffff", :hcolor => "55d9cb", :acolor => "35b9ab", :bcolor => "173f4f", :project => "openSUSE:Tools", :package => "osc", :format => "iframe" %>" width="100%" height="700px" frameBorder="0" ></iframe>
</div>
